{
  "texts": [
    "Further supporting this, Ahmed et al. [62] noted that concrete mixes containing up to 10% RHA achieved compressive strengths exceeding 40 MPa within just 7 days, indicating strong early-age strength.",
    "Additionally, Obokparo and Arum [63] demonstrated that a mix containing a combination of 10% RHA with coconut husk ash (CHA) increased compressive strength by 16.1%, showing the potential of RHA to enhance strength when used with other materials.",
    "Moreover, Sakr et al. [64] reported increased compressive strength in heavyweight concrete.",
    "Studies have shown that replacing cement with GGBFS generally improves concrete mechanical properties and durability.",
    "Yun et al. [65] found that GGBFS replacements at 20%, 40%, and 50% by weight increased compressive strength by 3-5%, 41.17%, and 25%, respectively, after 28 days, while also enhancing flexural strength by 10-15% and resistance to chemical attacks."
  ]
}